claim.claim-text:
1. A surgical tool holding mechanism including a linear drive device comprising: a threaded shaft; a motor coupled to the threaded shaft and configured to drive rotation of the threaded shaft; and a carrier fitted to the threaded shaft by a clutch mechanism, the clutch mechanism being for use with the carrier of the linear drive device, the clutch mechanism comprising:
a housing;
a first gear coupled to the housing and having gear teeth configured to engage a threaded shaft of a linear drive device, rotation of the shaft causing said housing to move along the shaft in a first mode of operation;
a first clutch arrangement associated with the first gear and configured to prevent substantial rotation of the first gear with respect to the housing when a rotational force applied to the first gear is less than a threshold force and to permit rotation of the first gear with respect to the housing when a rotational force applied to the first gear is greater than the threshold force, said housing being manually moved along a length of the shaft, in a second mode of operation, by exerting a force on the housing, said rotational force being applied to the first gear through the interaction of the threaded shaft and the gear teeth exceeds the first threshold, wherein the surgical tool holding mechanism includes:
an attachment arrangement attached to the carrier and configured to receive an endoscope or endoscopic surgical tool;
a second gear coupled to the housing and having gear teeth configured to engage a shaft of a linear drive device, a path suitable to receive a shaft of a linear drive device being defined between the first and second gears; and
a second clutch arrangement associated with the second gear and configured to prevent substantial rotation of the second gear with respect to the housing when a rotational force applied to at least one of the gear teeth of the second gear is less than a threshold force and to permit rotation of the second gear with respect to the housing when a rotational force applied to the second gear is greater than the threshold force, said housing being moveable along the shaft by rotation of the shaft of a linear drive device in a first mode of operation and manually moveable along a length of the shaft in a second mode of operation.
